Create a Batch Data Transform

You can create a batch data transform with data lake objects or data model objects.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
USER PERMISSION SETS
NEEDED
To create batch data transforms:	

Any one of these permission sets:

Data Cloud Admin
Data Cloud for Marketing Admin
Data Cloud for Marketing Data Aware Specialist
In Data Cloud, on the Data Transforms tab, click New.
If the Data Transforms tab isn’t visible, click More and select Data Transforms.
Select Batch Data Transform, and then click Next.
Select the data source.
If you selected data model objects as the source, select a data space from the dropdown menu. The data transform output applies only to the specified data space.
NOTE A data transform that runs on data model objects is restricted to a data space. You can't associate a data transform that runs on data lake objects with a data space.
Select the initial input data for the batch data transform.
Click Add Input Data, and select the objects that you want to add.
Under Selected Columns, choose which of the object’s columns to include in your input data, or select Name to select all columns.
If you added multiple source objects, select each object one at a time and then choose its columns. Selected Columns shows only the columns for the selected object.
Click Next.
An input node for each input data selection is added to the canvas.
Add a node to the batch data transform by clicking the Add Node button () between two nodes or at the end of the batch data transform. Then, select the node type.
To show the Add Node button between two nodes, hover the cursor on the connecting line.
Preview the results of each node and transformation that you added by selecting the node or transformation in the canvas.
To edit or delete a node, select the node, click , and then select the appropriate action. To edit or delete a transformation in a Transform node, select the Transform node, select the transformation step, and then click  or .
To connect, join, or append nodes in the canvas, drag the Add Node button () next to a node or Branch button () on top of another node in the canvas. Select one of the Connect Nodes options.
End the data transform with one or more output nodes.
If your data source is a data lake object, select the object to write the results to, and then click Apply.
If your data source is a data model object, select the object to write the results to or create a new object.
